Package tools.event

Class Key

  • java.lang.Object
    • tools.event.Key
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, PublicCloneable
    public class Key
extends java.lang.Object
implements PublicCloneable
    Class containing shorter and clearer naming for keys and masks all under one roof instead of spread out over multiple classes.

      • setMask

        public Key setMask​(int mask)
        Sets the mask of this key or having the same mask value.
        If the current key is not immutable, then the value of this is changed. Otherwise, a new object is created with the same values as this, but with the new mask set.
        Returns:
        A key having the same key value as key and the given mask.

      • applyMask

        public Key applyMask​(int mask)
        Adds the mask to the key. The mask is added with the OR-operation.
        If the current key is not immutable, then the value of this is changed. Otherwise, a new object is created with the same values as this, but with the new mask applied.
        Returns:
        A key having the same key value as key, but with the new generated mask.

      • newKeyValue

        public Key newKeyValue​(int k)
        Sets the key value of this key.
        If the current key is not immutable, then the value of this is changed. Otherwise, a new object is created with the same values as this, but with the new key value set.
        Returns:
        A key having the same properties as this, but has the given key value.

      • setOnKeyRelease

        public Key setOnKeyRelease​(boolean okr)
        Sets the on key release value.
        If the current key is not immutable, then the value of this is changed. Otherwise, a new object is created with the same values as this, but with the new on key release value set.
        Returns:
        A new key having the same properties as this, but has the given onKeyRelease value.

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(java.lang.Object obj)
        Checks if two keys are identical, i.e. the key, mask, onKeyRelease and immutable fields are compared.

        Also returns true if:
        • obj is a Number, and the integer value of this number is equal to the key value.
        • obj is a KeyStroke, and the key and mask value are equal.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object

      • parse

        public static Key parse​(java.lang.String source)
                 throws java.text.ParseException
        Parses the given string to a Key object.

        The format used must be the same as the toString() function:
        'class'['field_1'='value_1', ... ,'field_n'='value_n']
        with:
        • class: the value of Key.class.getCanonicalName()
        • field_x: the name of field 'x'.
        • value_x: the value of field 'x'.

        Moreover, the for any non-null key key holds that:
        Key.parse(key.toString()).equals(key)
        Parameters:
        source - The string to parse.
        Returns:
        A Key object from the parsed string.
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException - if the given string was invallid.
